This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel model for learning from weak labels using consistency regularization, which is a popular concept in semi-supervised learning. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing supervised learning models in solving the LLP problem. 

The paper also involves image classification experiments, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. 

Additionally, the paper discusses the use of bag-generation and validation-based parameter-selection procedures, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) categories.
